         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">(a monk) accuses (another monk) of SA.-sin (without ground), he commits Pāt.-sin. ///</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a1 #a2 #a3 #a4 #a5 #b1 #b2 #b3 #b4 #b5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:couvreur1954a"/><citedRange>50</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:broomhead1962"/><citedRange>82-83</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">goes on one way through agreement, ultimately even through from a village to a village ///</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">goes on one way through agreement, ultimately even through (from a village to a village) ///</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">to the man under twenty years old ///</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4 #a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>333</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1997"/><citedRange>99</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">he will not to be ordained. These monks ought all to be blamed. ///</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[digs] or orders another man to dig, (he commits) Pāt.-sin. (73) ///</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">invited continuously, invited again and again ///</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">(he commits) Pāt.-sin. [74] If a monk ///</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">(I will not) learn here by the speech of you who are fool, ///</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>74</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">I will ask someone who has learned Sūtra, Vinaya, Abhidharma and Āgamas ///</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
