            <p>&lt;project_comment&gt;&lt;p&gt;Translation according to &lt;bibl&gt;&lt;title corresp="ref:broomhead1962"/&gt;&lt;citedRange&gt;82-83&lt;/citedRange&gt;&lt;/bibl&gt;: &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;a1 (Whichever monk) accuses (a monk) of a (saṃ)ghāvaśeṣa crime (without reason)commits a pāyti crime. 69. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;a2 (Whichever monk) goes on a journey (with a woman after agreement) even only from one village to the [next] village (commits a pāyti crime). 70. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;a3 (Whichever monk with thieves) after agreement goes on a journey even only (from one village to the next village) (commits a pāyti crime) 71. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;a4 (Whichever monk performs the consecration) of one under twenty (commits a pāyti crime). The latter &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;a5 shall not be consecrated [and] all the monks are to blame. 72. (Whichever monk with his own hand) digs (the ground) &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;b1 or orders another to dig [it] (commits) a pāyti crime. 73. (For four months a monk can accept a personal invitation, but should he accept for longer than this) &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;b2 except when he is constantly and again and again invited &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;b3 commits a pāyti crime. 74. Whichever (monk, when the Prātimokṣa sūtra is being recited, speaks in this manner) &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;b4 "(I shall not) here learn from the word of ignorant ones [such as] ye, [but] &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;b5 I shall ask such as know the Sūtra, the Vinaya, the Abhidharma and the Āgamas, having learnt them." (commits a pāyti crime.)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;bibl&gt;&lt;title corresp="ref:broomhead1962"/&gt;&lt;citedRange&gt;83&lt;/citedRange&gt;&lt;/bibl&gt; contains further notes on text and translation.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/project_comment&gt;</p>
